+# Wine Stock Report Generator
+
+A command-line tool that converts a warehouse stock-on-hand CSV file into a readable Markdown stock report.
+
+The report summarizes finished wine stock, dry goods, available stock, allocated stock, pack sizes, vintage, variety, market, low-stock warnings, and data quality warnings.
+
+## Usage
+
+### Non-interactive mode (for automation)
+
+```bash
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter examples/stock_sample.csv --no-interactive
+```
+
+### Interactive mode (default)
+
+```bash
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter examples/stock_sample.csv
+```
+
+The interactive mode will ask you clarification questions about report options before generating the report.
+
+## Command-line Options
+
+- `CSV_PATH` — Path to the stock CSV file (required)
+- `--basis {OnHand,Available}` — Stock quantity basis for wine totals (default: `Available`)
+- `--group-by {variety,vintage,market,pack_size,lot,none}` — Grouping dimension for summary (default: `variety`)
+- `--include-dry-goods` / `--no-dry-goods` — Include or exclude Dry Goods section (default: include)
+- `--low-stock-warnings` / `--no-low-stock-warnings` — Enable or disable low-stock warnings (default: enabled)
+- `--low-stock-threshold N` — Low-stock threshold in 9-litre-equivalent units (default: `10`)
+- `--output PATH` — Output file path (default: `stock-report.md`)
+- `--no-interactive` — Skip interactive prompts and use effective option values
+
+## Examples
+
+Generate a report with OnHand basis instead of Available:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter stock.csv --basis OnHand --no-interactive
+```
+
+Generate a report grouped by vintage:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter stock.csv --group-by vintage --no-interactive
+```
+
+Exclude dry goods and set a lower low-stock threshold:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter stock.csv --no-dry-goods --low-stock-threshold 5 --no-interactive
+```
+
+## Input CSV Format
+
+The CSV file must contain these required columns:
+
+- `Type1` — Row type: `Finished Goods` or `Dry Goods`
+- `Item` — Item ID
+- `Description` — Item description (parsed for wine metadata)
+- `OnHand` — On-hand quantity
+- `Warehouse` — Warehouse name
+- `Allocated` — Allocated quantity
+- `Pending` — Pending quantity
+- `Available` — Available quantity
+- `Units` — Unit type: `Cases` or `Eaches`
+
+Optional columns:
+
+- `ClientStockCode` — Client-specific stock code
+- `ClientStockDescription` — Client-specific description
+- `Lot` — Lot identifier
+
+## Report Output
+
+The report is generated in Markdown format and includes:
+
+1. **Header** — Generation date, source file, warehouse, and stock basis
+2. **Executive Summary** — Row counts, total wine stock (9LE), case totals, and lowest-stock item
+3. **Grouping Section** — Summary by variety, vintage, market, pack size, or lot (unless `--group-by none`)
+4. **Detailed Finished Goods** — Table with all wine items and their metrics
+5. **Low Stock Warnings** — Items below the low-stock threshold
+6. **Dry Goods Summary** — All dry goods rows in original units (when included)
+7. **Data Warnings** — Issues detected during processing
+
+## Wine Description Parsing
+
+The parser extracts metadata from wine descriptions in the format:
+
+```
+FV <vintage> <variety_code> <brand_code> <market> <bottle_size>ml/<pack_size>p [extra description]
+```
+
+Example: `FV 22 CHR EP NZ 750ml/12p`
+
+Parsed as:
+- Prefix: `FV`
+- Vintage: `22` (expanded to `2022`)
+- Variety code: `CHR` (mapped to `Chardonnay`)
+- Brand code: `EP`
+- Market: `NZ`
+- Bottle size: `750ml`
+- Pack size: `12`
+
+### Variety Code Mappings
+
+- `CHR` → Chardonnay
+- `SAB` → Sauvignon Blanc
+- `PIN` → Pinot Noir
+- `PIG` → Pinot Gris
+- `PRO` → Rosé
+- `RDB` → Red Blend
+- `MXD` → Mixed / Consolidated
+
+Unknown variety codes are preserved and flagged in data warnings.
+
+## 9-Litre-Equivalent (9LE) Calculation
+
+9LE represents standard wine case equivalents:
+
+```
+9LE = (Quantity × Pack Size × Bottle Size in litres) / 9
+```
+
+For example:
+- 750ml/12p case = 9LE (1 standard case)
+- 750ml/6p case = 0.5 9LE (half case)
+
+## Testing
+
+Run the test suite:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest discover -s tests
+```
+
+The test suite includes:
+- CSV loading tests
+- Wine description parser tests
+- 9LE calculation tests
+- Validation tests
+- CLI integration tests
+- Report generation tests
+
+## Requirements
+
+Python 3.11+ with standard library only (no external dependencies).
